<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../../../helpproject.xsl" ?>
<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Joint</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Joints<keyword>Ball-Joint</keyword><keyword>Pin-Joint</keyword><keyword>Slide-Joint</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Kinematic-Pairs</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Joint</text> is equivalent to a <text style="font-style:italic;">&apos;Constraint&apos;. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Each<text style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Joint</text> constrains how two <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Part">Parts</link> move relative to each other.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">In <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="font-style:italic;">MechDesigner</text><text style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">*</text>, there are three joints:</para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint</text> - identical to a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Revolute-Joint</text>, the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">R</text> Joint in a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Dyad</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Slide-Joint</text> - identical to a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Prismatic-Joint</text>, the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">P</text> Joint in a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Dyad</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Ball-Joint</text> - identical to a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Spherical-Joint</text>, the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">S</text> Joint in a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Dyad</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The letters <text styleclass="VariableName-small">R</text>, <text styleclass="VariableName-small">P</text> and <text styleclass="VariableName-small">S</text> refer to <text styleclass="VariableName-small">R</text>evolute, <text styleclass="VariableName-small">P</text>rismatic and <text styleclass="VariableName-small">S</text>pherical, respectively.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;">*</text> There are more joints that <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="font-style:italic;">MechDesigner</text> does not provide. However, they are rarely found in Packaging or Assembly Machines.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Pin-Joint">Pin-Joint</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Slide-Joint">Slide-Joint</link>, <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Ball-Joints">Ball-Joint</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
